{
  "doc_id": "53986",
  "text": "There is controversy about whether mildly decreased levels of PS or PC are associated with an increased risk of VTE [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Levels of PS and PC activity are usually 35-60% and 35-65%, respectively, in heterozygous deficiency, whereas the majority of healthy individuals have levels of 70-130% [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . Kinoshita et al. reported that PS activity of patients with deep vein thrombosis with a gene mutation varied from 10% to 60%, and PC activity of patients with deep vein thrombosis with a gene mutation varied from 18% to 63% [CITATION_8] .",
